I am a strong believer that relationships can work. It takes a lot of time, patience and love when you merge two unique personalities together. The key I believe is when it no longer becomes about "me" but "us". Make quality time for each other, even if it means putting down the phone, turning off the TV or changing an activity of two. In the end it will be worth it.

First off I love dnd - I started with dnd in 83. I love A lot of rpgs and I have played many and worked on many more. The original OGL gave a lot of creators a chance to play in a world we grew up in. Something special… these creators brought their own fan bases to 5e and help that game grow into what it is only to see an open system promised them to be torn up in their faces. I’ve worked on a lot of 3rd party supplement and I will tell you a lot of the content created dwarfs what was coming out… and it was for a game we love. Until the suits got involved, who have never played nor do they understand it’s roots or it’s fans.

So now that this might change - I am standing with the 3rd party publishers. Let’s create a truly open world that gives creators a chance to help build a world and help support families. I think the idea is marvelous and I hope to see something come from it. 

Will I still give 5e a chance - yes I will - I really enjoy the system - but things need to change before I buy more of the stuff.

So here is my banner, my beacon and my support as a creator #pathfinder #koboldpress #mcdm Cawood Publishing/Fantasy RPG company !

29 years ago, yesterday, two kids started on their biggest adventure. I'm grateful to have had Travis by my side as I've grown (in all the ways 🙃🤣) and experienced all that life has had to offer over the years. Together we have faced this rollercoaster of life and I'm so very thankful.  What started with two youngin's has grown to 5  beautiful children, 4 amazing bonus kiddos, 5 adorable grandbabies and don't forget the fur babies! 
Yesterday I woke up to sunflowers in a vase (I'm telling you, he spoils me) and we celebrated with our baby-see awkward selfie lol- by going to see the latest Studio Ghibli film, a Barnes & Noble and World Market trip, some Chipotle for dinner along with Lego building and Across the Spider-Verse. A very geeky and lovely anniversary celebration, indeed 💕 I love you, Mr. Hanson
